> I have to admit that I find the idea rather tempting too. On the
> other hand, is there anything this would do that an automounter
> wouldn't ?
You can continue using the data on that filesystem or have
processes which have a directory on one the filesystem as
their current directory.
(Say, an editor with one of the source code files from such
a disk in its buffer...)
